snippet.textDisplay: Online articles and the media have perpetuated fear over the virus without fact checking ahead of time to even thoroughly explain what the virus does to those who are unaware, and certified health professionals are not being heard because hygienic industries are profiting off of peoples' paranoia. There are around 4,000 people who have died, but there are around 30,000 who have recovered that news headlines fail to mention, and the death toll is also not taking into account the healthcare available to certain countries who may not have as good healthcare as other countries and are thus more susceptible. This virus is not something new; it has existed since around 8000 BCE with multiple variations and outbreaks over the centuries, and while this is the worst outbreak by far, more people still die from the flu each year. If you're a hygienic person and try to avoid those who are sick whenever feasible, you're not likely to get the virus if you take care of yourself and have common sense.
